From cb13936d9df270ad2871df5f8b20f36b5d50ee9f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 21 May 2026 14:18:57 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Add tiered Stage 3 critic with structured per-field
 verdicts

Replaces the two-field Sonnet-only critic with a tier dispatcher that
runs Haiku presence checks on title/year/eis_type/agency/alt names and
Sonnet grounded-reasoning checks on summary/alt descriptions/stance/
themes/location/historical_internal. Sonnet "no" verdicts retry on
Opus up to OPUS_RETRY_BUDGET_PER_DOC. Under critic-budget pressure
tiers shed Opus -> Sonnet -> Haiku; deterministic gates always run.

Adds CriticVerdict/CriticValidation to the schema as a side-channel on
EISRecord so existing field models are unchanged. Legacy downgrade
behavior on summary.status and historical_context_internal.status is
preserved. Writes a critic_summary.json sidecar next to the token
ledger for per-field pass-rate monitoring across runs.
